# =============================================================================
# USAGE INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================
# 1. Copy this file as .env
#    cp env.example .env
#
# 2. Modify values according to your environment
#    - Change database credentials
#    - Change JWT secrets
#    - Adjust ports if necessary
#
# 3. For local development, you can use default values
#    - Default values are configured for development
#
# 4. For production:
#    - Change ALL secrets
#    - Use a real database
#    - Configure HTTPS
#    - Adjust timeouts and limits
#
# 5. Run tests:
#    ./test-coverage.sh
#
# 6. Run the application:
#    go run main.go
#
# =============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# =============================================================================
# ⚠️  NEVER commit .env with real secrets
# ⚠️  Use environment variables in production
# ⚠️  Rotate secrets regularly
# ⚠️  Use HTTPS in production
# ⚠️  Configure firewalls and network security
# ⚠️  Monitor logs and metrics
